<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Posts | Pedro Carrott</title><link>https://pcarrott.github.io/post/</link><atom:link href="https://pcarrott.github.io/post/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><description>Posts</description><generator>Wowchemy (https://wowchemy.com)</generator><language>en-us</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><image><url>https://pcarrott.github.io/media/icon_hu2f40df1e36ee708a3b980cca86548b45_2432_512x512_fill_lanczos_center_3.png</url><title>Posts</title><link>https://pcarrott.github.io/post/</link></image><item><title>How to make a website like this</title><link>https://pcarrott.github.io/post/create-site/</link><pubDate>Mon, 26 Sep 2022 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://pcarrott.github.io/post/create-site/</guid><description>&lt;p>This website was made by the &lt;a href="https://wowchemy.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Wowchemy&lt;/a> website builder using the Hugo &lt;a href="https://github.com/wowchemy/starter-hugo-academic" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Academic Resumé Template&lt;/a>. Wowchemy provides a simple guide for creating and deploying your website in &lt;a href="https://www.netlify.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Netlify&lt;/a>.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>This website, however, is hosted on &lt;a href="https://pages.github.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub Pages&lt;/a>. While both services provide a free plan, GitHub Pages offers unlimited build minutes, unlike Netlify. I also prefer the default URL domain of GitHub Pages.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>In this post, I will describe step-by-step how you can do the same for your website. All you need is a GitHub account and you&amp;rsquo;re all ready to go!&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="create-the-repository">Create the repository&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Open the &lt;a href="https://github.com/wowchemy/starter-hugo-academic" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Academic Theme repository&lt;/a> and click on the green button saying &lt;em>Use this template&lt;/em>. You will be asked to create a new repository which you should name &lt;em>username&lt;/em>.github.io, where &lt;em>username&lt;/em> is your GitHub username.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>Alternatively, you can create a repository with same name and copy the contents of the Academic Theme to this new repository.&lt;/p>
&lt;h2 id="setup-the-repository">Setup the repository&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>In &lt;code>config/_default/config.yml&lt;/code> change the &lt;code>baseURL&lt;/code> field to &lt;code>https://&amp;lt;username&amp;gt;.github.io&lt;/code> and create a file named &lt;code>.github/workflows/gh-pages.yml&lt;/code> with the following contents:&lt;/p>
